utm_source=rss&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=whos-been-detained-in-lebanon-for-freedom-of-speech";s:10:"post_title";s:55:"Who’s been detained for freedom of speech in Lebanon?";s:10:"post_image";s:68:"http://www.smex.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Freedom-of-Speech.png";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:123:"Photo credit: www.sha3teely.com
In the last few years,  journalists, artists, activists, and others in Lebanon have bee...";s:7:"blog_id";s:4:"smex";s:14:"post_timestamp";i:1399133040;s:12:"post_content";s:895:"<div><a href="http://www.smex.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Freedom-of-Speech.png"><img src="http://www.smex.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Freedom-of-Speech.png" alt="" width="800" height="449"></a><p>Photo credit: www.sha3teely.com</p></div>
<p>In the last few years,  journalists, artists, activists, and others in Lebanon have been detained or  spent some time on trial for freedom of expression under different laws. This is a list of names starting 2009 that we find in our research. Please get in touch if you want to add more names we missed. Note that this list will covers only the detainees and the people who spent time on trial. <iframe src="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1fd4uVVFkrIIBS-gnL2xKcMkGByQwX51ugzy5Gl1C-N4/pubhtml?widget=true&headers=false" width="610" height="366" frameborder="0"></iframe></p>
<p>This research was done by Joey Ayoub and Mohamad Najem</p>";s:17:"post_image_height";i:449;s:16:"post_image_width";i:800;s:11:"post_visits";i:13;s:18:"post_twitterShares";i:8;s:19:"post_facebookShares";i:0;s:16:"post_totalShares";i:8;s:16:"post_socialScore";i:22;s:13:"post_virality";i:17;s:9:"blog_name";s:4:"SMEX";s:16:"blog_description";s:19:"Channeling Advocacy";s:8:"blog_url";s:15:"http://smex.org";s:11:"blog_author";s:7:"Various";s:28:"blog_author_twitter_username";s:4:"SMEX";s:13:"blog_rss_feed";s:25:"http://www.smex.org/feed/";s:9:"blog_tags";s:15:"activisim, tech";s:2:"id";i:129;s:11:"blog_active";i:1;s:24:"blog_last_post_timestamp";i:1401511740;}i:7;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:7:"post_id";i:28881;s:8:"post_url";s:77:"http://mustapha.me/2014/05/quick-hack-read-annahars-pdf-edition-on-your-ipad/";s:10:"post_title";s:53:"Quick Hack: Read Annahar’s PDF edition on your iPad";s:10:"post_image";s:75:"http://mustapha.me/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/annahar-ipad-before-after.jpg";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:123:"I was hesitating to share this with you as I had meant it for my personal use only. But it’s very useful and I don’t...";s:7:"blog_id";s:8:"mustapha";s:14:"post_timestamp";i:1399127640;s:12:"post_content";s:1980:"<p>I was hesitating to share this with you as I had meant it for my personal use only. But it’s very useful and I don’t think I’m hurting <em>Annahar</em> in anyway when I share this. So here goes.</p>
<p>I like reading my news on the iPad each morning, and I’m not really a fan of <em>Annahar’s</em> iPad edition, which for all intents and purposes has become <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abandonware">abandonware</a>; I also love the Layout of <em>Annahar</em> and I think <a href="http://www.linotype.com/5282/nadinechahine.html">Nadine</a> has done <a href="http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20110411007222/en/Customized-Typeface-Lebanon%E2%80%99s-An-Nahar-Newspaper-Debuts-Redesign#.U2T7761_urY">tremendous work</a> with the fonts.</p>
<p>All this is to say that I want a way to see <em>Annahar</em> in all its layout and typography glory on my iPad. But the <a href="http://newspaper.annahar.com/pdf">official way</a> of browsing the pdf in <em>Annahar’s</em> website is very lacking on the iPad, which still is not friendly to embedded PDFs in iframes. So I wrote a little script that will just load the pdf file of the latest edition of the newspaper and fill the entire iPad screen. See the difference: </p>
<p><a href="http://tools.mustapha.me/annaharpdf"><img src="http://mustapha.me/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/annahar-ipad-before-after.jpg" alt="Annahar ipad before after" title="annahar-ipad-before-after.jpg" border="0" width="600" height="396"></a></p>
<p>So how can you make use of it? Easy, just bookmark <a href="http://tools.mustapha.me/annaharpdf">this link</a> and voila: <a href="http://tools.mustapha.me/annaharpdf">http://tools.mustapha.me/annaharpdf</a></p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://mustapha.me/2014/05/quick-hack-read-annahars-pdf-edition-on-your-ipad/">Quick Hack: Read Annahar’s PDF edition on your iPad</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://mustapha.me/">Mustapha Hamoui's Geek Blog</a>.</p>";s:17:"post_image_height";i:396;s:16:"post_image_width";i:600;s:11:"post_visits";i:17;s:18:"post_twitterShares";i:3;s:19:"post_facebookShares";i:7;s:16:"post_totalShares";i:10;s:16:"post_socialScore";i:26;s:13:"post_virality";i:18;s:9:"blog_name";s:27:"Mustapha Hamoui's Geek Blog";s:16:"blog_description";s:39:"Tech, Coffee & other exciting things…";s:8:"blog_url";s:18:"http://mustapha.me";s:11:"blog_author";s:15:"Mustapha Hamoui";s:28:"blog_author_twitter_username";s:12:"beirutspring";s:13:"blog_rss_feed";s:24:"http://mustapha.me/feed/";s:9:"blog_tags";s:13:"tech, society";s:2:"id";i:288;s:11:"blog_active";i:1;s:24:"blog_last_post_timestamp";i:1401280800;}i:8;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:7:"post_id";i:28847;s:8:"post_url";s:75:"http://tech-ticker.com/huawei-smartphones-now-officially-available-lebanon/";s:10:"post_title";s:54:"Huawei Smartphones Now Officially Available in Lebanon";s:10:"post_image";s:0:"";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:123:"Cherfane Trading Company (Chetraco) launched Huawei smart phones in Lebanon during a press conference that took place a...";s:7:"blog_id";s:11:"tech-ticker";s:14:"post_timestamp";i:1399057560;s:12:"post_content";s:5111:"<p>Cherfane Trading Company (Chetraco) launched Huawei smart phones in Lebanon during a press conference that took place at Le Royal Hotel, in the attendance of a crowd of Technology and lifestyle journalists to discover and experience the smartphones which made an impression on the Android market globally.</p>
<p>“<em>Today we welcome the Huawei smartphones to the unique, multi faceted national distributor Chetraco family alongside other brands such as kelvinator, Candy, JBL/Harman Kardon, TCL, Midea and Fratelli Onofri. Chetraco proved to be an efficient, cost-effective distribution partner for its manufacturers and national customer base and we are highly optimistic in the positive results that will be achieved with Huawei’s addition to Chetraco’s portfolio</em>.” said Mr. Eddy Cherfane, CEO of Chetraco.</p>
<p>Huawei is a <a href="http://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/~en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multinational_corporation">multinational</a> networking and <a href="http://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/~en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telecommunications_equipment">telecommunications equipment</a> and services company and it is the largest telecommunications equipment maker in the world. Its Consumer Business Group is committed to creating the most innovative, user friendly smartphones in the world, that made it achieve the 3<sup>rd</sup> place in global smartphones market share, securing its place as a leader in the smartphone business.</p>
<p><em>“The smartphones market in the Middle East is rapidly evolving and Huawei is expanding its regional footprint steadfastly. We are forging strong ties with local distributors in every market, leveraging their knowledge of local consumer demands and our latest innovations in smartphone technologies</em>“, noted Ashraf Fawakherji, Vice President Middle East Device Business.</p>
<p>Known for the world’s slimmest smart phone, the passionately anticipated Huawei mobiles join the Android smartphones family available for consumers in Lebanon, through Chetraco distributors.</p>
<p>“<em>Lebanon is a small yet important market for smartphones; it is where the latest technology gets adopted early due to the avant-garde nature of the Lebanese consumers. What we are launching today, really takes just an implausible quantum leap forward for Chetraco and for the smartphone market in Lebanon”, a</em>dded Cherfane.</p>
<p>Mr. Elia Haj Elias, Devices Sales and Marketing Manager of Huawei phones in the Levant, showcased the various models in the Huawei mobile phones range, highlighting the state-of-the-art technology and distinctive design, features and specifications of the phones.</p>
<ol><li>30% more power saving than any other phone in its segment.</li>
<li>25% faster charging than any other phone in its segment.</li>
<li>Innovative design for ease of use, high durability, and Unique Identity.</li>
<li>Emotion UI, Huawei’s own flavor of android customization built for Ease of use and high personalization.</li>
</ol><p>The Huawei devices will initially be made available at Cherfane Trading approved suppliers shops all over Lebanon. We will follow up on the matter and keep you updated with Huawei news.</p>
