";i:2;s:18:"post_twitterShares";i:1;s:19:"post_facebookShares";i:1;s:16:"post_totalShares";i:2;s:16:"post_socialScore";i:5;s:13:"post_virality";i:6;s:9:"blog_name";s:11:"Tech Ticker";s:16:"blog_description";s:154:"A Technology and gadget online magazine, stuffed with news and reviews of the latest devices and gadgets. Tech-Ticker is headquartered in Beirut, Lebanon.";s:8:"blog_url";s:23:"http://tech-ticker.com/";s:11:"blog_author";s:11:"Tech-Ticker";s:28:"blog_author_twitter_username";s:15:"techtickertweet";s:13:"blog_rss_feed";s:38:"http://feeds.feedblitz.com/tech-ticker";s:9:"blog_tags";s:4:"tech";s:2:"id";i:139;s:11:"blog_active";i:1;s:24:"blog_last_post_timestamp";i:1401717360;}i:12;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:7:"post_id";i:28789;s:8:"post_url";s:107:"http://lfadi.wordpress.com/2014/05/01/yougotagift-pleasantness-for-someone-and-tranquility-for-another-one/";s:10:"post_title";s:79:"“YouGotaGift” – Pleasantness for someone and tranquility for another one.";s:10:"post_image";s:48:"http://lfadi.files.wordpress.com/2014/04/011.jpg";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:123:"What kind of gifts should I offer her on Valentine’s day? What is the best gift I can buy him for his birthday?
Choosi...";s:7:"blog_id";s:5:"lfadi";s:14:"post_timestamp";i:1398971880;s:12:"post_content";s:4042:"<p>What kind of gifts should I offer her on Valentine’s day? What is the best gift I can buy him for his birthday?</p>
<p>Choosing the appropriate gift is one of the most difficult problems everyone faces. Cash gifts are surely the easiest and less time-wasting especially when no idea what to buy. Thus, the gift cards were founded to avoid gifting cash which may be misconstrued as if it is negligent or disrespectful.</p>
<p><a href="http://lfadi.files.wordpress.com/2014/04/011.jpg"><img src="http://lfadi.files.wordpress.com/2014/04/011.jpg?w=300&h=225" alt="01" width="300" height="225"></a></p>
<p> </p>
<p>However, buying a gift card needs time; furthermore it may limit the diversity of choice. Here from comes the idea of an eGift card, a gift card that can be bought online in few minutes to be used in 55+ stores like Virgin Megastore, Galerie Lafayette, Boutique 1, Faces, iStyle, etc.</p>
<p>What can be fluffier and prettier than receiving a message telling you got a gift?!</p>
<p><a href="http://lfadi.files.wordpress.com/2014/04/13.png"><img src="http://lfadi.files.wordpress.com/2014/04/13.png?w=700" alt="1"></a></p>
<p> </p>
<p>The instant messaging “YouGotaGift” is the first online mall for gift cards in the Middle East. It was launched in UAE and extended to Lebanon recently.</p>
<p>Regardless of your current residence, you can now send an eGift Card to the one you care about living in Lebanon and he will be able to use it at any of the partners’ store. For the time being, YouGotaGift website is fairly adjusted for smartphones, awaiting the iPhone and Android applications that should be available within couple of weeks in addition to audio and video messaging tools.</p>
<p><a href="http://lfadi.files.wordpress.com/2014/04/23.png"><img src="http://lfadi.files.wordpress.com/2014/04/23.png?w=700" alt="2"></a></p>
<p> </p>
<p>You pick the eGift Card from the website by setting the amount, defining the occasion, selecting the design (a note and a photo can be added to the card) and choosing the delivery type (“Print at Home” for a printed hard copy of the card to be gifted and “Send it Digitally” for a soft copy to be sent via SMS, Email or Facebook):</p>
<p><img src="http://lfadi.files.wordpress.com/2014/04/43.png?w=700&h=235" alt="4" width="700" height="235"></p>
<p>Once done, you enter the payment details (Visa card, Master card or PayPal):</p>
<p><a href="http://lfadi.files.wordpress.com/2014/04/62.png"><img src="http://lfadi.files.wordpress.com/2014/04/5.png?w=700" alt="5"></a></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Moreover, YouGotaGift provide many services like “Group Gifting” and “Weddings”:</p>
<p><img src="http://lfadi.files.wordpress.com/2014/04/34.png?w=700&h=286" alt="3" width="700" height="286"></p>
<p> </p>
<p>As mentioned on the website, the purchase is instant, on time and secure. Once the purchase done, the message will be directly sent to the concerned person unless it is scheduled at a specific date and time. The card is usable since purchasing and for one year.</p>
<p><img src="http://lfadi.files.wordpress.com/2014/04/62.png?w=700" alt="6"></p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<p>Below the interview with YouGotaGift co-founder Abed Bibi:</p>
<p><span><iframe type="text/html" width="700" height="424" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/Js8ap9p9BEY?version=3&rel=1&fs=1&showsearch=0&showinfo=1&iv_load_policy=1&wmode=transparent" frameborder="0"></iframe></span></p>
<p> </p>
<p>P.S.: <em>The content of this blog reflects my own opinion about YouGotaGift after a quick review. Any contrary opinion is more than welcomed especially if the commentator already used the service.</em></p>
