<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.taknologia.com/snapchat-now-offers-im-videochat-self-destruct/">Snapchat now offers IM and Videochat with self destruct</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.taknologia.com/">taknologia</a>.</p>";s:17:"post_image_height";i:360;s:16:"post_image_width";i:480;s:11:"post_visits";i:4;s:18:"post_twitterShares";i:1;s:19:"post_facebookShares";i:10;s:16:"post_totalShares";i:11;s:16:"post_socialScore";i:14;s:13:"post_virality";i:19;s:9:"blog_name";s:22:"Taknologia | Tech Blog";s:16:"blog_description";s:89:"We stride to write the most interesting pieces of technology that interest you the most. ";s:8:"blog_url";s:25:"http://www.taknologia.com";s:11:"blog_author";s:0:"";s:28:"blog_author_twitter_username";s:11:"takno_logia";s:13:"blog_rss_feed";s:31:"http://www.taknologia.com/feed/";s:9:"blog_tags";s:4:"tech";s:2:"id";i:290;s:11:"blog_active";i:1;s:24:"blog_last_post_timestamp";i:1401707160;}i:14;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:7:"post_id";i:28783;s:8:"post_url";s:83:"http://www.absolutegeeks.com/2014/05/foursquare-splits-into-two-say-hello-to-swarm/";s:10:"post_title";s:46:"Foursquare splits into two: Say hello to Swarm";s:10:"post_image";s:71:"http://www.absolutegeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/swarm_group.jpg";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:123:"In what may seem initially confusing, Foursquare is splitting itself into two distinct apps: Swarm and Foursquare.
The m...";s:7:"blog_id";s:13:"absolutegeeks";s:14:"post_timestamp";i:1398961620;s:12:"post_content";s:1757:"<p>In what may seem initially confusing, Foursquare is splitting itself into two distinct apps: Swarm and Foursquare.</p>
<p>The move comes after careful investigation of how users engage with the app and the result of the endeavour to decrease app bloat. Swarm app – launching for iOS, android, and Windows Phone (at a later stage) – is your check-in and friend-finding app. It is aimed to be simple, fast, and efficient with a focused goal: find where your friends are and check in.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.absolutegeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/swarm_group.jpg" rel="lightbox-0"><img src="http://www.absolutegeeks.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/swarm_group.jpg" alt="swarm_group" width="710" height="508"></a></p>
<p>The Foursquare app itself will be re-invented to focus on discovery. Foursquare describes this as the digital Yellow Pages:</p>
<blockquote><p><span>Local search today is like the digital version of browsing through the Yellow Pages (remember those?). We believe local search should be personalized to your tastes and informed by the people you trust. The opinions of actual experts should matter, not just strangers.</span></p></blockquote>
<p>For an in-depth dive, check out the detailed coverage on <a title="Meet Swarm: Foursquare's ambitious plan to split its app in two" href="http://www.theverge.com/2014/5/1/5666062/foursquare-swarm-new-app" target="_blank">The Verge</a>.</p>
<div>
					<div>Source: <a href="http://blog.foursquare.com/post/84422758243/a-look-into-the-future-of-foursquare-including-a-new">Foursquare</a>; <a title="Meet Swarm: Foursquare's ambitious plan to split its app in two" href="http://www.theverge.com/2014/5/1/5666062/foursquare-swarm-new-app" target="_blank">The Verge</a></div></div>";s:17:"post_image_height";i:730;s:16:"post_image_width";i:1020;s:11:"post_visits";i:14;s:18:"post_twitterShares";i:6;s:19:"post_facebookShares";i:1;s:16:"post_totalShares";i:7;s:16:"post_socialScore";i:22;s:13:"post_virality";i:16;s:9:"blog_name";s:14:"Absolute Geeks";s:16:"blog_description";s:28:"Unleash The Tech Geek In You";s:8:"blog_url";s:24:"http://absolutegeeks.com";s:11:"blog_author";s:0:"";s:28:"blog_author_twitter_username";s:13:"absolutegeeks";s:13:"blog_rss_feed";s:34:"http://www.absolutegeeks.com/feed/";s:9:"blog_tags";s:4:"tech";s:2:"id";i:268;s:11:"blog_active";i:1;s:24:"blog_last_post_timestamp";i:1401602040;}i:15;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:7:"post_id";i:28775;s:8:"post_url";s:74:"http://www.absolutegeeks.com/2014/05/google-docs-and-sheets-arrive-to-ios/";s:10:"post_title";s:36:"Google Docs and Sheets arrive to iOS";s:10:"post_image";s:0:"";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:123:"Google has just launched standalone apps for Google Docs and Google Sheets for iPhone and iPad – both for free. The ap...";s:7:"blog_id";s:13:"absolutegeeks";s:14:"post_timestamp";i:1398942420;s:12:"post_content";s:1012:"<p>Google has just launched standalone apps for <a title="Google Docs – Apple AppStore" href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/google-docs/id842842640?mt=8" target="_blank">Google Docs</a> and <a title="Google Sheets – Apple AppStore" href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/google-sheets/id842849113?mt=8" target="_blank">Google Sheets</a> for iPhone and iPad – both for free. The apps are also available on android as part of <a title="Google Docs – Google Play" href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.google.android.apps.docs.editors.docs&referrer=utm_source%3Dblog%26utm_campaign%3Dannouncement" target="_blank">Google Docs</a>.</p>
<p>The free solution is a direct stab at Microsoft’s paid offer on iOS, and for most users the functionality of the free apps will suffice. You can view, create, and edit your documents offline and sync whenever you are online.</p>
<div>
					<div>Source: <a href="http://googledrive.blogspot.co.uk/2014/04/docssheetsapps.html">Google</a></div></div>";s:17:"post_image_height";i:0;s:16:"post_image_width";i:0;s:11:"post_visits";i:3;s:18:"post_twitterShares";i:2;s:19:"post_facebookShares";i:1;s:16:"post_totalShares";i:3;s:16:"post_socialScore";i:8;s:13:"post_virality";i:9;s:9:"blog_name";s:14:"Absolute Geeks";s:16:"blog_description";s:28:"Unleash The Tech Geek In You";s:8:"blog_url";s:24:"http://absolutegeeks.com";s:11:"blog_author";s:0:"";s:28:"blog_author_twitter_username";s:13:"absolutegeeks";s:13:"blog_rss_feed";s:34:"http://www.absolutegeeks.com/feed/";s:9:"blog_tags";s:4:"tech";s:2:"id";i:268;s:11:"blog_active";i:1;s:24:"blog_last_post_timestamp";i:1401602040;}i:16;O:8:"stdClass":26:{s:7:"post_id";i:28742;s:8:"post_url";s:64:"http://mustapha.me/2014/04/the-day-i-stopped-reading-newspapers/";s:10:"post_title";s:36:"The Day I Stopped Reading Newspapers";s:10:"post_image";s:67:"http://mustapha.me/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/reading-newspaper.jpg";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:123:"Today, April 30th, 2014 is the day I will officially mark as the day I stopped reading newspapers. It’s kind of a big ...";s:7:"blog_id";s:8:"mustapha";s:14:"post_timestamp";i:1398883680;s:12:"post_content";s:1644:"<p><img src="http://mustapha.me/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/reading-newspaper.jpg" alt="Reading newspaper" title="reading-newspaper.jpg" border="0" width="600" height="373"></p>
<p>Today, April 30th, 2014 is the day I will officially mark as the day I stopped reading newspapers. It’s kind of a big deal for me, since I used to love spreading a broadsheet on a table with a coffee in hand and some nice jazz music playing softly in the background. But today is the day I found out I no longer wanted that.</p>
<p>You see, I did realize in the past few years that I was reading less and less newspapers and more and more online news or Kindle dailies, but I always assumed that it was out of pragmatic necessity, because I didn’t have access to an actual paper. But it turns out the transformation was more permanent.</p>
<p>Today, I was having breakfast at the hotel, and I saw them: A set of fresh, untouched, free newspapers silently pleading to me to pick them up and read while I’m having my morning coffee. These were not some second tier cheap newspapers. No, they were Lebanon’s top dailies: Annahar, the Daily Star..etc. This was a sight (and smell) that the old me would have drooled over, but today I felt nothing. </p>
<p>I hesitated for a moment, then looked at my iPhone, and it hit me: It’s officially the end of an era. I no longer want to read any news printed on paper…</p>
